Arthur's gaze lingered on the mahogany expanse, where Sir Alistair's limp hand rested near a heavy silver brandy flask, its cap unscrewed, a telling white residue clinging to its rim. Beneath the desk's sharp corner, a small scrap of green silk ribbon, unmistakably from a masquerade costume, had snagged as if in a frantic retreat. These grim details presented themselves with stark clarity, inviting closer scrutiny of the room and its silent occupant.

> 
[Hint] Next beat: A Room Disturbed — The Study

